    <title>
      <string language="en">Leadership &amp; Professionalism </string>
    </title>
    <language>en</language>
    <description>
      <string language="en">What is this course about?

This course is designed to equip members of the Theme Park &amp; Toy Engineers (TPTE) and aspiring leaders with the essential &quot;soft skills&quot; required to excel in the themed entertainment and toy industries. While technical skill is the &quot;what&quot; of your career, professionalism and leadership constitute the &quot;how&quot; and the &quot;why.&quot; Professionalism isn&#039;t just about wearing a suit or showing up on time; it’s a standard of conduct. It encompasses accountability, respect, and ethical decision-making. Leadership is the ability to guide, inspire, and coordinate people toward a common goal. It’s not reserved for people with &quot;Manager&quot; in their title; it’s an attitude.</string>
    </description>
